<br>
If you are thinking of server transferring, let me offer you a couple of friendly hints so you can avoid some of the problems others have had:<br>
<br>
1.) Be nice. Yes this is a pvp server, but it's not Sullon Zek. If you transfer from a blue server enamored of the idea of killing other players, and spend a couple of days doing that because you can, you'll have problems. Most of the people in the larger 65+ guilds have been around a long time. Word of a cross-server dork travels fast. If you're coming because you want non-stop pvp, you'll be disappointed.<br>
<br>
2.) Try to make friends, do LDONs and trials and just otherwise get to know us or whatever guild you app here if you transfer. <br>
<br>
3.) Avoid making problems with one of the larger guilds, even if those problems are not PVP driven. On rallos reputation is everything. You'll have one chance to make yours, don't blow it.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll add to that:<br>
<br>
- you can kill or be killed by anyone +/- 4 levels of you.<br>
<br>
- you are not pvp enabled until level 6.<br>
<br>
- on RZ, you can loot 1 item and all money if you get the kill shot or are killed by someone.<br>
<br>
- items in bags or in your hands/range cannot be looted.<br>
<br>
